<subSubSection id="D4E0654CFFF4FD0DFF700D53B2D7F9A6" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph id="9C4536C7FFF4FD0DFF700D53B011FAFB" blockId="2.[151,604,1266,1327]" box="[151,573,1301,1327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
(
<figureCitation id="04C12A42FFF4FD0DFF780D53B2DEFAFB" box="[159,242,1301,1327]" captionStart="PLATE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,238,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[244,1318,207,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-98@4.[240,1326,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="PLATE 2 (isthmia and granadensis). 1,2. Brassolis isthmia isthmia female, PANAMÁ: Taboga Island, BMNH. 3,4. Brassolis isthmia isthmia Lectotype male, PANAMÁ: Lion Hill, BMNH. 5,6. Brassolis granadensis Paralectotype female, COLOMBIA: Río Magdalena, BMNH. 7,8. Brassolis granadensis Lectotype male, COLOMBIA: Río Magdalena, BMNH. 9,10. Brassolis isthmia daisye Holotype female, COLOMBIA: Chicorral, BMNH. 11,12. Brassolis isthmia daisye Paratype male, COLOMBIA: Mariquita, UPI. 13,14. Brassolis isthmia wallengreni Holotype female, ECUADOR: Paramba, BMNH. 15,16. Brassolis isthmia wallengreni Paratype male, ECUADOR: Tinalandia, BMNH" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5125057" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5125057/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Plate 2</figureCitation>
, figs. 1–4; 
<figureCitation id="04C12A42FFF4FD0DFE910D53B3EBFAFB" box="[374,455,1301,1327]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,238,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,194,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-116@9.[226,1360,194,1740]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="PLATE 3 (details). 1,2. Brassolis granadensis female, COLOMBIA: Otanche, JFL. 3. Brassolis granadensis male, COLOMBIA: Río Magdalena, BMNH. 4,5. Brassolis isthmia isthmia female, PANAMÁ: Taboga Island, BMNH. 6. Brassolis isthmia isthmia Lectotype male, PANAMÁ: Lion Hill, BMNH. 7,8. Brassolis isthmia daisye Paratype female, COLOMBIA: Chaparral, ICNO. 9. Brassolis isthmia daisye Paratype male, COLOMBIA: Mariquita, UPI. 10,11. Brassolis isthmia wallengreni Paratype female, ECUADOR: Tinalandia, CRB. 12. Brassolis isthmia wallengreni Paratype male, ECUADOR: Balzapamba (Paralectotype male of Brassolis granadensis), BMNH. 13. Brassolis haenschi haenschi male ECUADOR: Macas, ZMUC. 14. Brassolis haenschi haenschi male ECUADOR: Macas, ZMUC. 15. Brassolis haenschi haenschi male ECUADOR: Macas, ZMUC." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5125059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5125059/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Plate 3</figureCitation>
, figs 4–6)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C4536C7FFF4FD0DFF700D23B2D7F9A6" blockId="2.[151,1436,1381,1650]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
The description of 
<taxonomicName id="5BFA4D44FFF4FD0DFE9F0D23B3E2FAAA" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1864" box="[376,462,1381,1406]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Brassolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isthmia">
<emphasis id="AE8EEAD5FFF4FD0DFE9F0D23B3E2FAAA" box="[376,462,1381,1406]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">isthmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on 
<specimenCount id="8AFCFD4EFFF4FD0DFD990D23B0DAFAAB" box="[638,758,1381,1407]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
from Lion Hill, 
<collectingCountry id="E4ED7657FFF4FD0DFC5A0D23B632FAAB" box="[957,1054,1381,1407]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Panamá</collectingCountry>
. In the BMNH Type Collection, there are 
<specimenCount id="8AFCFD4EFFF4FD0DFEE30DCBB352FA73" box="[260,382,1421,1447]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
; the one with the additional label ‘figured specimen’ is designated 
<typeStatus id="43418865FFF4FD0DFB6A0DCBB6D5FA73" box="[1165,1273,1421,1447]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="04C12A42FFF4FD0DFAEF0DCBB770FA73" box="[1288,1372,1421,1447]" captionStart="PLATE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,238,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[244,1318,207,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-98@4.[240,1326,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="PLATE 2 (isthmia and granadensis). 1,2. Brassolis isthmia isthmia female, PANAMÁ: Taboga Island, BMNH. 3,4. Brassolis isthmia isthmia Lectotype male, PANAMÁ: Lion Hill, BMNH. 5,6. Brassolis granadensis Paralectotype female, COLOMBIA: Río Magdalena, BMNH. 7,8. Brassolis granadensis Lectotype male, COLOMBIA: Río Magdalena, BMNH. 9,10. Brassolis isthmia daisye Holotype female, COLOMBIA: Chicorral, BMNH. 11,12. Brassolis isthmia daisye Paratype male, COLOMBIA: Mariquita, UPI. 13,14. Brassolis isthmia wallengreni Holotype female, ECUADOR: Paramba, BMNH. 15,16. Brassolis isthmia wallengreni Paratype male, ECUADOR: Tinalandia, BMNH" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5125057" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5125057/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Plate 2</figureCitation>
, figs. 3&amp;4). Male nominate 
<taxonomicName id="5BFA4D44FFF4FD0DFE440DF3B3D5FA1A" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1864" box="[419,505,1461,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Brassolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isthmia">
<emphasis id="AE8EEAD5FFF4FD0DFE440DF3B3D5FA1A" box="[419,505,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">isthmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="E4ED7657FFF4FD0DFDC30DF3B0ADFA1B" box="[548,641,1461,1487]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Panamá</collectingCountry>
have a distinct orange streak alongside Cu 
<subScript id="007E3482FFF4FD0DFB6F0D83B6BCFA07" attach="left" box="[1160,1168,1477,1491]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">2</subScript>
on the hindwing. The range of the nominate taxon is generally regarded as extending from 
<collectingCountry id="E4ED7657FFF4FD0DFC5C0DA6B61FFA2E" box="[955,1075,1504,1530]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
to the 
<collectingRegion id="5E3EF825FFF4FD0DFB640DA6B6E0FA2E" box="[1155,1228,1504,1530]" country="Colombia" name="Cauca" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Cauca</collectingRegion>
Valley in 
<collectingCountry id="E4ED7657FFF4FD0DFAA50DA6B297F9F6" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F86B4B36FFF4FD0DFF2C0E4EB349F9F6" author="Stichel, H" box="[203,357,1544,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" pagination="244" refId="ref6146" refString="Stichel, H .. (1909) Brassolidae. Das Tierreich, 25, xiv, 244." type="journal article" year="1909">Stichel 1909</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F86B4B36FFF4FD0DFE940E4EB39EF9F6" author="Stichel, H." box="[371,434,1544,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" refId="ref6199" refString="Stichel, H. (1932) Brassolidae. Lepidopterorum Catalogus, 51." type="book" year="1932">1932</bibRefCitation>
). Nominate 
<taxonomicName id="5BFA4D44FFF4FD0DFDA30E4EB0B6F9F5" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1864" box="[580,666,1544,1569]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Brassolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isthmia">
<emphasis id="AE8EEAD5FFF4FD0DFDA30E4EB0B6F9F5" box="[580,666,1544,1569]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">isthmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, if it does occur in 
<collectingCountry id="E4ED7657FFF4FD0DFC600E4EB1D2F9F6" box="[903,1022,1544,1570]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, is probably confined to the northwest, but I have seen no undoubted specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="E4ED7657FFF4FD0DFD080E76B14AF99E" box="[751,870,1584,1610]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Colombia</collectingCountry>
; there is, however, 
<specimenCount id="8AFCFD4EFFF4FD0DFBAF0E76B69EF99E" box="[1096,1202,1584,1610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
in the MNHN from ‘Cauca’.
</paragraph>
